records.addlTxt:
Defendant John Derrick Carson in court with attorney Joel Alan Mogren.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 6 months in the House of Correction with credit for 0 days time served; Huber privileges for work, treatment and medical.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 year.
Conditions:
*  Serve 30 days in the House of Correction; sentence stayed and to be used at the discretion of the agent for any violations;
*  Pay restitution in the amount of $204.95 to Sentry by June 8, 2016 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Pay a fine of $150.00 plus all costs and surcharges by September 12, 2017 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  No contact with Sentry Foods;
*  Maintain full time employment;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge.  
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
